</chemistry>
<br/>
(b) HO&#x2014;(CH<sub>2</sub>)<sub>3</sub>&#x2014;OH, a natural diol made from corn;
<br/>
(c) a fatty alcohol conforming to the following structure:
<br/>
<?in-line-formulae description="In-line Formulae" end="lead"?>HO&#x2014;(CH<sub>2</sub>)<sub>b</sub>&#x2014;CH<sub>3 </sub><?in-line-formulae description="In-line Formulae" end="tail"?>
<br/>
b is an integer ranging from 6 to 31 or mixtures thereof.
</p>
<p id="p-0034" num="0033">Where there are two different types of ester group present, one liquid (C6-C10) and one solid (C12-C31), the resulting structure cannot crystallize completely, since the liquid domains in the polymer act as molecular crystal distorters, resulting in a polymer that although having the same melting point, flows more easily when pressure is applied. The resulting solid will be soft and flowable, rather than hard and un-yielding.</p>
