<p id="p-0052" num="0051">To a suitable reactor equipped with heating and an ability to distill off water is added the specified number of grams of citrate acid (Example 1), next is added the specified number of grams of the fatty alcohol (Examples 3-21). The reaction mass is heated to 150-160&#xb0; C. and water is distilled off. As the reaction proceeds, the batch clears and free citric acid is reacted out. The reaction mass is kept at this temperature until the acid value becomes vanishingly low. Next is added the specified number of grams of the specified 1,3 propane diol (Examples 2). The reaction mass is heated to 180-190&#xb0; C. and water is distilled off. The reaction mass is kept at this temperature until the acid value becomes vanishingly low. The reaction mass is cooled and used without additional purification.</p>
